The paper discusses the empirical evaluation of algorithms for learning Bayesian network classifiers, which is a topic related to machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also involves conditional independence-based algorithms, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases).
